headlines.description: — Four wins in the final week sent the Brooklyn Nets surging up to seventh in the Eastern Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets beat Pacers to lock up 7th, host play-in game Tuesday
Hornets top Wizards 124-108, fail to improve play-in seeding

headlines.description: — The Milwaukee Bucks used the final game of the regular season to rest up before defending their NBA crown.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavs blast Bucks backups 133-115 to earn No. 8 play-in seed

headlines.description: — Atlanta coach Nate McMillan is certainly glad his team's season didn't end Sunday with the regular-season finale.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hawks beat Rockets 130-114 but stay in 9th spot for play-in

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 31 points, Jaylen Brown added 18 and the Boston Celtics secured the second seed in the East with a 139-110 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Sunday night in the regular-season finale for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics finish 2nd in East with 139-110 win over Grizzlies

events.name: Toronto Raptors at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Obi Toppin and Immanuel Quickley wanted to end the New York Knicks' disappointing season on a strong note.
headlines.shortLinkText: Toppin, Quickley have career nights as Knicks win finale

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid and James Harden are off to Toronto for the playoffs. Defensive specialist Matisse Thybulle is staying behind for the road games; he's not fully vaccinated and barred from entering Canada.
headlines.shortLinkText: 76ers win without Embiid, Harden, earn No. 4 seed in East

headlines.description: — Patrick Williams scored a career-high 35 points and Ayo Dosunmu had 26 points in a season-high 45 minutes as the Chicago Bulls hung on for a 124-120 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Sunday night with both teams in rest-the-regulars mode in...
headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls beat Wolves 124-120 behind Patrick Williams' 35 points

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic wouldn't have even played in what turned out to be a meaningless regular-season finale for the playoff-bound Dallas Mavericks without a reprieve from the NBA.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic injury puts playoff status in doubt as Mavs top Spurs

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Malik Monk had a career-best 41 points and Austin Reaves set career highs with 31 points, 16 rebounds and 10 assists to lead the Los Angeles Lakers to a 146-141 overtime victory over the Denver Nuggets on Sunday night in what might have been Frank...
headlines.shortLinkText: Reaves, Monk lead Lakers past Nuggets 146-141 in OT

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Amir Coffey had career highs of 32 points and 13 rebounds, and the Los Angeles Clippers routed the depleted Oklahoma City Thunder 138-88 on Sunday night to end the regular season on a five-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rout OKC 138-88 for 5th win in row, play-in awaits

events.name: Golden State Warriors at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson punctuated his regular season with a fist pump — a display of emotion stemming from far more than his latest flurry of fourth-quarter points.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thompson scores 41, Warriors top Pelicans to clinch 3rd seed

headlines.description: — The Sacramento Kings just finished a dismal year, which has been a common theme for the franchise over the last 16 seasons.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings hang on to beat Suns 116-109 in regular-season finale

events.name: Utah Jazz at Portland Trail Blazers
